The article discusses the upcoming trip of the First Lady, Michelle Obama, to Japan and Cambodia. The trip is focused on the Let Girls Learn initiative, which aims to address the barriers that prevent over 62 million girls around the world from receiving an education. In Japan, the First Lady will meet with Japanese officials and highlight the commitment of Japan to girls' education. In Cambodia, she will meet with high school students and community leaders to see how community-led programs are improving girls' education. The First Lady will also use social media and online tools to engage with young people in the United States and raise awareness about the importance of education for girls globally. The trip is part of the broader U.S. strategy of rebalancing towards the Asia-Pacific region.